320 g Chicken Breast Tenders
100 g Rice Noodles
1 unit Mini Cucumber
56 g Carrot, julienned
1 unit Lime
28 g Baby Spinach
1 unit Green Onion
2 tbsp Sweet Chili Sauce
28 g Peanuts, chopped
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, bring a large pot of water to a boil over high.
Lightly oil the grill. While you prep, preheat the grill to medium-high (approx. 425°F).
Wash and dry all produce.
To the boiling water, add rice noodles. Cook for 10-12 min, stirring occasionally, until tender but still slightly chewy to the bite.
While noodles cook, thinly slice cucumber.
Juice lime.

To a small bowl, add soy sauce, lime juice, half the sweet chili sauce and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Stir to combine.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels. To a shallow dish, add chicken and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lime-soy dressing. Season with salt and pepper. Flip to coat.

Add chicken to the grill. Reduce heat to medium, then close lid and grill for 2-4 min per side, until chicken is cooked through.**
Drain rice noodles and rinse under warm water until slightly cool. Return to the pot.
To the pot of noodles, add spinach, cucumber, carrots, peanuts and remaining lime-soy dressing. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine.

Using two forks, shred chicken.
Divide noodles between bowls.
Top with chicken.
Drizzle with remaining sweet chili sauce and snip green onion over top.